    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">22</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice Checkpoint</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Tracing Claims to Evidence</h2><ul><li>Identify the source of a claim about the Ingalls family</li><li>Evaluate the reliability of the supporting evidence</li><li>Flag unsupported or weakly supported assertions</li><li>Reflect on how source quality affects conclusions</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This practice slide helps learners apply source criticism skills by tracing claims about the Ingalls family back to their evidence and assessing reliability. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Given a claim from a secondary source, locate the primary source cited and evaluate its strength.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Select a claim from provided materials and trace it to its original source; assess its credibility.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Accepting claims without verifying their evidentiary basis.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide22\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which source type provides the most direct evidence about the Ingalls family&#39;s role in the 1692 witch trials?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;Primary court records and trial transcripts&quot;,&quot;Modern historical interpretations&quot;,&quot;Family folklore and oral traditions&quot;,&quot;Popular media dramatizations&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;Primary court records and trial transcripts are original documents from the time of the trials and offer direct evidence, unlike later interpretations or folklore.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain why it is important to use cautious language when summarizing the Ingalls family&#39;s involvement in the Salem witch trials.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;The answer should mention the limits of historical records, potential biases in sources, name confusion, and the need to avoid overstating uncertain or unsupported claims.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Because historical records about the Ingalls family are incomplete and sometimes conflicting, cautious language helps avoid presenting uncertain or disputed information as fact.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Historical records are incomplete and biased, so cautious language prevents overstating facts.&quot;,&quot;Name confusion and missing evidence require careful wording to avoid misleading conclusions.&quot;,&quot;To reflect uncertainty and avoid presenting unverified claims as truth.&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
